    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "## Problem\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.o.number = true\n\nlocal api = vim.api\nlocal buf0 = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\napi.nvim_buf_call(\n  buf0,\n  function()\n    vim.fn.jobstart({ 'echo', '00000000000' }, {\n      term = true,\n    })\n  end\n)\n\nlocal float_opts =\n  { width = 10, height = 10, style = 'minimal', relative = 'editor', row = 5, col = 5 }\nlocal split_opts = { style = 'minimal', split = 'below', win = -1 }\n\n-- ok\n-- local win = api.nvim_open_win(buf0, true, split_opts)\n\nlocal win = api.nvim_open_win(buf0, true, float_opts)\napi.nvim_win_set_config(win, split_opts)\n\nlocal buf1 = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\napi.nvim_buf_call(\n  buf1,\n  function() vim.fn.jobstart({ 'echo', '11111111111111111111' }, { term = true }) end\n)\n--\napi.nvim_win_set_buf(win, buf1)\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nsplit window shouldn't enable `&number`.\n\nEDIT: `vim._with({ wo = { number = vim.wo.number } }, function() api.nvim_win_set_buf(win, buf1) end)` fix the issue\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-1877 ge1aceb0068` neovim/neovim@e1aceb0068\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.17.9-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
