            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I took another look at this and I think my previous comment is wrong. `get_winopts()` already re-applies minimal style:\n```c\n  if (curwin->w_config.style == kWinStyleMinimal) {\n    didset_window_options(curwin, false);\n    win_set_minimal_style(curwin);\n  }\n```\nHowever, when a float is changed to a split it's config is removed:\n```c\n    // non-floating window doesn't store float config or have a border.\n    merge_win_config(&wp->w_config, WIN_CONFIG_INIT);\n```\nThis was initially added in <https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/c8acbe3b623a4d7636e88b30f779c03845cf548f>, before the addition of `style`, so I'm not sure if the current behavior is intentional or not.\n\ncc @bfredl",
